2026-05-21 | Longest Common Prefix Between Two Arrays

	Question
Return length of longest common prefix.
	Key Insight
Instead of comparing every pair completely:
		store all prefixes of arr1 numbers in a set.
Then:
		check prefixes of arr2 numbers.
	Approach
1.	For every number in arr1:
		generate all prefixes
		store in hash set
2.	For every number in arr2:
		generate prefixes
3.	If prefix exists in set:
		update answer with prefix length
4.	Return maximum length found
	Time Complexity
	O(total digits)
	Space Complexity
	O(total prefixes)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int longestCommonPrefix(vector<int>& arr1,
                            vector<int>& arr2) {
        unordered_set<string> st;
        // store prefixes of arr1
        for(int x : arr1){
            string s = to_string(x);
            string pref = "";
            for(char c : s){
                pref += c;
                st.insert(pref);
            }
        }
        int ans = 0;
        // check prefixes of arr2
        for(int x : arr2){
            string s = to_string(x);
            string pref = "";
            for(char c : s){
                pref += c;
                if(st.count(pref)){
                    ans = max(ans,
                              (int)pref.size());
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
The problem becomes easy once viewed as:
		prefix matching problem  
Hashing all prefixes allows:
		fast lookups and efficient comparison.
